- cs.DS (Dynamical Systems): The paper studies the behavior of Max-Product and Max-Plus systems, which are types of dynamical systems.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): Although not directly related to machine learning, the paper uses Lyapunov functions, which are commonly used in machine learning for stability analysis.
- cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper uses stochastic processes and probability theory to analyze the stability of the systems, which are topics within the Information Theory sub-category.
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis): The paper provides a numerical example to illustrate the application of the stability results, which falls under the Numerical Analysis sub-category.
